"""
finance_transition_risk.py
==========================
Transition-Risk Financial Scenario Analysis
Facility: KWB Belchatow lignite mine  |  Issuer: PGE Polska Grupa Energetyczna S.A.

Class hierarchy
---------------
BaseTransmissionChannel       Abstract base — defines the P&L computation contract.
    CarbonCostChannel         Channel 1: Implied carbon-cost exposure under EU ETS pricing.
    CreditSpreadChannel       Channel 2: Bond mark-to-market from credit spread widening.
    EquityRepricingChannel    Channel 3: Equity P&L from a share-price shock.

TransitionRiskAnalyzer        Top-level orchestrator. Accepts evidence, issuer, channels,
                              price cases, and stress tiers; builds the full payload;
                              prints the scenario report; and saves JSON output.

This module is a stylized scenario analysis, not a predictive market forecast.
Equity and credit-spread shocks are illustrative stress tiers from the academic
transition-risk literature. They are not calibrated to PGE's historical return
distribution or implied volatility surface.

Usage
-----
    cd methane-api
    python scripts/finance/finance_transition_risk.py

Output
------
    scripts/results_analysis/finance_transition_risk.json

References
----------
Reinders, Schoenmaker & van Dijk (2025): "A finance approach to climate stress testing"
EU Regulation 2024/1787 on methane emissions in the energy sector.
IPCC AR5 / AR6 GWP factors for methane.
"""

